This paper deals with optimizing queries over a federation of SPARQL endpoints, which involves combining data from multiple sources. This is a common problem in the field of database systems (cs.DB), and the paper specifically addresses the challenges of optimizing such queries using statistical information. The use of statistics and cost estimation is also a common technique in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and optimization (cs.DC) research. The paper also deals with information retrieval (cs.IR) and data management (cs.DL) topics, as it involves querying and combining data from multiple sources.
